<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Inn1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Inn,</orth> 1) the town-house of a nobleman: <cit><quote>thou most beauteous i.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 1, 13</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) a college of common law professors and students: <cit><quote>a must to the --s o' court,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 14</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>Clement's i.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 14</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>Gray's i.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 14</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>in all the --s o' court,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 14</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.7.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 7, 2</bibl>.
<lb />3) a house of entertainment for travellers, a tavern: <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 14</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.93" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 3, 93</bibl> <cit><quote>(shall I not take mine ease in mine i.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 3.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 3, 7</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.265" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 265</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>